COMMENTS: SOURCE = MULTIPLE EMAILS, PHONE CALLS, AIRLINE, PACIR, AIR SAFETY WEEK, NEWS ARTICLE, ASRS xxxxxx
REMARKS: ID BY SMITHSONIAN FAA 914. (DATA ENTRY NOTE: LOTS OF CONFLICTING INFO ON THIS STRIKE.)  REPT FROM AIRLINE "CREW REPTD L ENG BIRDSTRIKE ON T/O. MX FOUND 1 STRIKE AT 9:00 POSITION ON RADOME NEAR BULKHEAD AND ON L WING INBD LE SLAT UPPER SURFACE. NO DMG. CLEANED DEBRIS." REPT FROM PRELIM INCIDENT REPT.- LCL TIME 2225E "A/C HAD A COMPRESSOR STALL IN THE #1 ENG CAUSING FLAMES TO SHOOT OUT. A/C IS DUMPING FUEL OVER LAKE MICHIGAN & WILL LAND AT ORD. ETA2308E. UPDATE #1. A/C BELIEVED TO HAVE EXPERIENCED A BIRDSTRIKE IN #1 ENG. A/C IS NOT DUMPING FUEL BUT WILL HOLD AND BURN OFF FUEL FOR ABOUT 2HRS." FINAL UPDATE: A/C LANDED RWY 14R W/O FURTHER INCIDENT AT 2338E." (DATA ENTRY NOTE: IF TIME OF STRIKE WAS 2225 AND THEY LANDED AT 2338, IT DID NOT TAKE 2 HRS TO BURN FUEL, SO MAYBE THEY DID DUMP IT). NOTES FROM WS BIOL AT ORD- "ENG WAS FERRIED TO SFO. ENG WAS SCOPED NEXT MORNING & FOUND NOTHING BUT IT HAD A COMPRESSOR STALL. HE COLLECTED FEATHERS AND TOOK PHOTOS OF SMEARS ON #1 ENG COWLING, RADOME AND LE OF WING. AIRLINE MX TOOK HIM TO THE A/C IN THE MORNING & SAID BORESCOPE FOUND NO INTERNAL PHYSICAL DMG. ANY DMG DONE WAS FROM HIGH INTERNAL TEMPS. MX WILL NOT KNOW UNTIL FURTHER TESTS ARE COMPLETED WHETHER OR NOT ANY FAN BLADES WILL BE REPLACED."  INFO FROM ALEX OROSZ AT AIRLINE SAID "ENG WAS CHANGED. ALSO SAID PILOT DUMPED 79,000 LBS (11,000 GALS) OF FUEL AND LANDED HEAVY. COST $15,000.  AIRLINE COST WAS $18,000 IN FEES FOR RETURNING TO LAND. CORE DAMAGE." ENG MANU- SAID "THE AIRLINE CONCLUDED THAT THERE WAS NO EVIDENCE OF ENGINE BIRD STRIKE AND THAT THEY MAY HAVE HIT A SOFT BLUNT OBJECT BUT NOTHING WAS INGESTED IN THE ENG."  ON JAN 14, AIRLINE SAID DEF NOT AN ENG REMOVAL. COST ONLY $4600. A/C WAS OUT OF SERVICE FOR 9 DAYS FOR MX BUT NOT BECAUSE OF BIRDSTRIKE. THERE WAS DEF A BIRDSTRIKE AND THERE WERE ENG PROBLEMS. BUT IT SEEMS THAT THE ENG PROBLEMS WERE NOT BIRD RELATED. ASRS REPT SAYS AT ABOUT 20 FT AFTER LIFTOFF, I FELT A STRONG YAW TO THE R INDICATIVE OF PWR LOSS ON THE L ENG. PROCEEDED TO FLY THE ENG OUT PROFILE. HEARD A SERIES OF LOUD BANGING NOISES & HAD NUMEROUS PWR FLUCTUATIONS. WE DETERMINED THESE WERE COMPRESSOR STALLS. DECLR EMERGENCY. DUMPED FUEL OVER LAKE MICHIGAN (ABOUT 20,000 LBS) STOPPED DUMP AND MADE OVERWT LDG AFTER DISCUSSION WITH DISPATCH. REPORTED SAID CAUSE OF L ENG FAILURE WAS 1 OR MORE BIRDS INGESTED INTO L ENG ON LIFTOFF.  ENG WAS REPLACED DUE TO COMPRESSOR DMG AND EGT EXCEEDENCE.
